<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1114,1318]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The first use of subgenera in 
<taxonomicName box="[519,635,1188,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[519,635,1188,1211]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Empoasca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was by DeLong (
<number box="[833,893,1186,1210]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1931.0">1931</number>
), but he did not recognize subgenera in his many subsequent papers on the genus. For a subgeneric diagnosis see Zhang et al. (
<number box="[1015,1077,1222,1246]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2008.0">2008</number>
).
</paragraph>
